x^2
\sin x
x^2
\frac{\sin x}{x} = (1 - \frac{x}{\pi})(1+\frac{x}{\pi})(1 - \frac{x}{2\pi})(1 + \frac{x}{2\pi})\dots = (1 - \frac{x^2}{\pi^2})(1 - \frac{x^2}{4\pi^2})\dots
1 - \frac{x^2}{3!} + \frac{x^4}{5!} - \dots
- \frac{1}{\pi^2} (1 + \frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{9} + \dots)
-\frac{1}{6}
(1 + \frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{9} + \dots) = \frac{\pi^2}{6}
